 Port Elizabeth - According to rainfall data released by the Port Elizabeth office of the South African Weather Service, most of the rain that fell on Monday was recorded in Uitenhage, Port Elizabeth and Cape St Francis. "The rainfall was mainly restricted to the coastal belt and adjacent interior around the Nelson Mandela Bay area," described Garth Sampson, SA Weather Service Client Liaison Officer for the Eastern Cape. Station Names 1 2 Nelson Mandela Bay   AWOS Port Elizabeth Airport 0.0 14.4 ARS 3rd Ave Dip NIL 16.2 ARS Blue Horizon Bay NIL 10.2 AWSH Chatty NIL 12.6 AWS Coega NIL 3.4 AWSH Fettes Road NIL 13.6 ARS Flower Reserve NIL 7.2 AWSH Motherwell NIL * ARS Riverstone Bridge NIL 16.8 ARS St Albans NIL 12.0 AWS Uitenhage NIL 16.2 Man Woodridge * 5.8 Catchment   AWS Joubertina 0.2 3.4 Man Kareedouw NIL * Man Kouga Dam NIL NIL AWS Patensie NIL 1.2 Man Swartkops  NIL 7.5 Man    Other Towns   AWS Addo NIL 0.2 AWS Bisho/KWT NIL 0.6 AWS Cape St Francis NIL 13.6 AWS Cradock NIL 0.4 AWS East London NIL NIL AWS Fort Beaufort NIL NIL AWS George 0.4 0.4 AWS Graaff Reinet NIL NIL AWS Grahamstown NIL 3.8 AWS Henry`s Flats NIL NIL AWS Joubertina NIL 3.4 AWS Mossel Bay NIL 1.0 AWS Mthatha NIL NIL AWS Plettenberg bay 0.4 6.2 AWS Port Alfred NIL 1.8 AWS Queenstown NIL 0.8 Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 